page.title: 01GENERAL REVIEW
page.content: THIS AREA IS TO THE NORTH -WEST OF BIRMINGHAM ON THE OLD BOUNDARY OF SUTTON COLDFIELD,WHICH WAS ONCE A ROYAL BOROUGH.THE AREA ,THEREFORE,DIVIDES UP INTO DISTINCT HOUSING TYPES ARRANGED AROUND THE ONCE ROYAL FOREST OF SUTTON PARK,A NATURAL WOODLAND AND HEATH AREA USED BY MANY PEOPLE IN THE AREA AS A PLACE OF RECREATION.ON THE NORTHERN EDGE ARE THE LARGE DETATCHED HOUSES OF THE SUTTON PEOPLE,A VERY MIDDLE CLASS AREA.TO THE SOUTH OF THE REGION IS A LARGE AREA OF COUNCIL OWNED PROPERTIES , WHILST IN THE MIDDLE ARE MOSTLY SEMI-DETACHED HOUSES WHICH ARE OWNER OCCUPIED THERE IS VERY LITTLE INDUSTRY IN THE AREA,PEOPLE EITHER TRAVEL TO WORK OR ARE INVOLVED IN THE SERVICE INDUSTRIES.
